Let's unify and win. 
 ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌

 

 

Kevin

I am really looking forward to meeting delegates at conventions this
weekend and later this month!

I must admit I am having a great time crisscrossing our beautiful state
from Worthington to Beaver Bay and points in between. When I am in the
car, I hum the Johnny Cash song, "I've been everywhere, man!"

Team Kim will be at all the county conventions meeting this month; 

**redistricting did not affect county-based BPOUs; we have been assured
that the convention calls were sent out to delegates on a timely
basis.**That is important.

(I had planned to be in Morrison County but that has wisely been
cancelled due to delegate list and other issues. We look forward to
visiting Morrison County once that has been resolved.)

And I hope this is helpful, especially to delegates who are new to the
process: 

**BPOUs that are not county-based were dissolved due to redistricting as
of February 15th; those BPOUs and MNGOP are working out the details of
delegate lists and convention calls. So stay tuned.**
Since I cannot be at all the county conventions meeting on the same day,
we are sending a "surrogate" in my place to read a short letter from me
whenever possible (you can find our letter here).

If you want to be a surrogate for me at any upcoming convention (not
just your own) please send an email (with subject line "Surrogate for
Kim") to info@KimSOS.com , and please sign up to
be a delegate here!  And we can
always use donations to help us WIN the endorsement!

I am so grateful to the volunteers who convened and helped at over 4,000
precinct caucuses. No one is getting paid as they juggle a life that
includes a serious commitment to active citizenship and the Republican
party. 

**Thank you!**

And I want to acknowledge the "elephant in the room." Our party is
working through serious issues around certain delegate lists; let me be
clear: any appearance of error or impropriety must be thoroughly
investigated and then resolved.

A first principle of leadership is seeking first to understand the facts
before we act. I am in communication with other candidates and party
leadership to sort out the facts and to help with a resolution.

Given that there are over 4,000 precincts reporting to 127 BPOUs, with
data then sent out by MNGOP, problems were predictable. 

**Especially during a redistricting year!**But they are perennial.

****We must commit as a party to work together to overhaul the process
in the future.

I beg my fellow Republicans to give Grace to all involved while holding
one another to the highest standards of conduct. The people of Minnesota
are watching us, weighing whether we are the leaders they are looking
for to lead our state out of the absolute train wreck of Democratic
rule.

Let's stick together and keep our eye on the prize: Victory in 2022
and governing the State of Minnesota in 2023!

With respect and affection,

Kim Crockett
Republican Candidate for Secretary of State

Candle in the Dark Gala Morehouse College Atlanta Georgia EFBBBFSaturday Feb 19 2022 930p Gambian 57th Independence Celebration Savannah Event Center College Park KEY DATES February 28 2022 End of the Month Fundraising Deadline April 25 2022 Voter registration deadline for Primary May 24 2022 Primary election date DONATE NOW LetE28099s Make History in Georgia February is Black History Month We have the opportunity to make history in Georgia in 2022 Our state is one of the most diverse states in the country and Georgians have the opportunity to elect leadership that reflects our diversity There has never been a Black person elected as Secretary of State in Georgia and I want to be the first Being among the firsts is not new to me I was among the first Blacks to desegregate the public elementary schools in Jacksonville Florida in 1969 I was the first in my family to graduate from an Ivy League University in 1987 and I was the second Black person ever elected as Chairman of Fulton County in 2006 Trailblazers have courage determination and perseverance and I have tried to embody these traits in every aspect of my personal professional and public life Over the past 7 months I have traveled throughout the State of Georgia and spoken with many Georgians of every walk of life Georgians want a Secretary of State who is fair experienced and has integrity ItE28099s time for a change and that time is 2022 As your next Secretary of State I will make voting accessible to all Georgians regardless of their race ethnicity social class or party affiliation I will fight for economic justice support small businesses and implement entrepreneurship training programs for young people In 2022 cast your vote for an experienced leader as your next Secretary of State Your vote for me is an investment for now and our childrenE28099s future LetE28099s make history in Georgia in 2022 Yours in Service Dr John Eaves Campaign Highlights EFBBBF Donate Give 22 to support John Eaves quotedprintableGood afternoon Freedom Fighters2CParents are frustratedThe pandemic did two things when it comes to education First2C it exposed what kids were learning Second2C it caused parents to rethink the educational setting where their child learns bestThe good news Arizona is a top state for education options and has been for 20 yearsArizonaE28099s Empowerment Scholarship Account ESAs removes barriers to access for children who would thrive in a setting other than their local district school It opens the doors to charter schools2C private school2C homeschooling2C learning therapies2C online academies2C and moreThe bad news Too many students are still boxed out of accessing optionsSome of the students boxed out of options are the ones who need it most students who have been victims of crimes in their public or charter schoolMy amendment to HB 2803 HB2803021422WMSEpdfmccid3Df58de7f26dmceid3DUNIQID creates a path for these students to access an ESA  and a learning environment where they can feel safe It establishes that an alleged victim of an offense occurring at a school or school related space2C is eligible for an ESA It also ensures proper policies and procedures to deal with these incidents within schoolsDONATE SO I CAN KEEP FIGHTING FOR YOU ckdonatemccid3Df58de7f26dmceid3DUNIQIDI have been fighting for a better education for the next generation from the start of my career Every child deserves an educational environment where they can thrive And2C as free market conservatives know so well2C competition improves the end productItE28099s time to remove the barriers that stand between kids and a better education ItE28099s a fight2C but IE28099m up for itI hope youE28099ll stand with me in this fight  and the one to come over all the other issues that matter for our future freedomsFor Arizona2CShawnna BolickSIGN MY PETITION2C GET ME ON THE BALLOT 3Df58de7f26dmceid3DUNIQIDJOIN MY CAMPAIGN texthtml charsetutf8ContentTransferEncoding quotedprintable Keeping kids 1 09 09090909090909 Good afternoonFreedom Fighters2C Parents are frustrated The pandemic did two things when it comes to education First2C it exposed what kids were learning Second2C it caused parents to rethink the educational setting where their child learns best The good news Arizona is a top state for education options and has been for 20 years ArizonaE28099s Empowerment Scholarship Account ESAs removes barriers to access for children who would thrive in a setting other than their local district school It opens the doors to charter schools2C private school2C homeschooling2C learning therapies2C online academies2C and morenbsp The bad news Too many students are still boxed out of accessing options Some of the students boxed out of options are the ones who need it most students who have been victims of crimes in their public or charter school My amendment to HB 2803 creates a path for these students to access an ESA  and a learning environment where they can feel safe It establishes that an alleged victim of an offense occurring at a school or school related space2C is eligible for an ESA It also ensures proper policies and procedures to deal with these incidents within schools 09090909 09090909 DONATE SO I CAN KEEP FIGHTING FOR YOU 09 09090909090909 I have been fighting for a better education for the next generation from the start of my career Every child deserves an educational environment where they can thrive And2C as free market conservatives know so well2C competition improves the end product ItE28099s time to remove the barriers that stand between kids and a better education ItE28099s a fight2C but IE28099m up for it I hope youE28099ll stand with me in this fight  and the one to come over all the other issues that matter for our future freedoms For Arizona2C 09090909 09090909 09 09090909090909 Shawnna Bolick 09090909 09090909 SIGN MY PETITION2C GET ME ON THE BALLOT JOIN MY CAMPAIGN          09 09090909 PAID FOR BY VOTE BOLICK AUTHORIZED BY SHAWNNA BOLICK 09090909 09090909 09 09090909090909 Copyright C2A9 2022 Vote Bolick2C All rights reserved Our mailing address is Vote Help us win 
 ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌

 

 

Kevin,

If we don't have elections we can trust, then nothing else matters.
Throughout this campaign, I've emphasized the NEED to get Eyes on Every
Ballot - so that we can spot cheaters and those who would disenfranchise
other legal voters in our state. It is NOT a partisan issue. Keith
Ellison and Tim Walz get the headlines, 

**but make no mistake: Steve Simon let the foxes into our henhouse**. He
courted Zuckerberg's money; he made up election law to favor his own
party; and in doing so he compromised our trust in the electoral
process.

If I'm elected as your Secretary of State, we will use our office to
advocate strongly for voter ID and provisional ballots, to end vouching,
and to stop ballot harvesting by terminating ballot drop-off boxes. I
pledge never to sign consent decrees which make our elections more
vulnerable to cheating. I respect our legislature and our Constitution. 

BUT I CANNOT DO THIS WITHOUT YOU. STEVE SIMON IS A DNC DARLING AND MONEY
IS ALREADY FLOODING INTO OUR STATE TO SUPPORT HIM. HELP US COMBAT THEIR
BIG MONEY WITH GRASSROOTS, SMALL DOLLAR DONATIONS.

We need to recruit field staff and shout it from the rooftops that
secure elections is one of the most pressing issues of our time. Steve
Simon's DNC buddies don't care about our state. They want to strip
safeguards from our elections because their lust for power relies on it!

I need you now to join me, stand up, and say "We need an expert on
elections in the Secretary of State's office!" Any amount you can RUSH
IN

right now will help propel us toward victory. The Secretary of State's
office is very consequential, and if we don't put someone in who knows
WHERE THE BODIES ARE BURIED - we cannot effectively clean house.

Stop ballot harvesting.
Stop Zuckerberg dollars.
Stop unreasonably long early voting.
Get voter ID.

Let's support a campaign that is dead serious about building trust in
our elections. Help us win!

Relying on you and thankful for your support,

Kim Crockett

Republican Candidate for Secretary of State

DONATE TODAY AND HELP US WIN!

birthday of Congressman John Lewis He was often referred to by President Barack Obama as being the soul of the Congress Even though the Congressman is no longer with us his legacy lives on Like my SEENGROSSEDpdfmccid3D0ff8ba7fa4mceid3DUNIQID 2C Emergency Bill to Secure Online PetitionsThis is an emergency bill which requires the Secretary of State to immediately rectify our online petition portal Many legislators are being held up from gathering petitions because the current Secretary of State2C Katie Hobbs2C isnE28099t doing her job as chief election official of Arizona Instead of serving the people like she was elected to do2C she is playing politics with the office and Arizonans are paying the priceHB2378 SEENGROSSEDpdfmccid3D0ff8ba7fa4mceid3DUNIQID 2C Prohibiting Damaging Settlements in Election LawsuitsThis bill prohibits the Secretary of State from settling a lawsuit without the consent of county recorders or election officers that would be affected by the lawsuit The Secretary of State shouldnE28099t be making unilateral political decisions when election laws are under dispute in the courtsHB2379 SEENGROSSEDpdfmccid3D0ff8ba7fa4mceid3DUNIQID 2C Requiring Transparency and Security of Election ProceduresThis bill is really important It requires that the election manualE28094which prescribes rules for fair2C impartial2C and efficient electionsE28094 conform to the rule of law in Arizona In 20202C election officials disregarded our election laws and wrote an election manual that was neither impartial nor in agreement with the statutes the legislature passed2E This bill closes that loophole and also requires electronic voting systems to be field checked and reviewed by experts This bill is currently in the Senate and awaiting committee IE28099ve been working on this session HB2703 2C Emergency Bill to Secure Online Petitions This is an emergency bill which requires the Secretary of State to immediately rectify our online petition portal Many legislators are being held up from gathering petitions because the current Secretary of State2C Katie Hobbs2C isnE28099t doing her job as chief election official of Arizona Instead of serving the people like she was elected to do2C she is playing politics with the office and Arizonans are paying the price HB2378 2C Prohibiting Damaging Settlements in Election Lawsuits This bill prohibits the Secretary of State from settling a lawsuit without the consent of county recorders or election officers that would be affected by the lawsuit The Secretary of State shouldnE28099t be making unilateral political decisions when election laws are under dispute in the courts HB2379 2C Requiring Transparency and Security of Election Procedures This bill is really important It requires that the election manualE28094which prescribes rules for fair2C impartial2C and efficient electionsE28094conform to the rule of law in Arizona In 20202C election officials disregarded our election laws and wrote an election manual that was neither impartial nor in agreement with the statutes the legislature passed This bill closes that loophole and also requires electronic voting systems to be field checked and reviewed by experts This bill is currently in the Senate and awaiting committee review and a vote IE28099m eager to see it passed and the mess of past elections cleaned upnbsp Thank is darkFrom Bee Nguyen ReplyTo infobeeforgeorgiacom5aa5vXYr0fFDcxH08evWw49621307661C1D126ContentTransferEncoding quotedprintableContentType textplain charsetUTF8February is Black History Month E28094 a time to honor the incredible achievements of Black Americans throughout our history while reflecting on the struggle and adversity that they faced to get there0D0A 0D0AWhile the nation celebrates Black History Month Georgia Republicans are pushing through House Bill 1084 legislation that censors educators and their ability to teach accurate history in the classroom During the committee hearing on this bill a Georgia lawmaker used Dr Martin Luther King Jr as a justification for the passage of this bill 0D0A 0D0AThis censorship bill is antidemocratic and infringes on the right of Americans to have the full freedom to engage in truthful conversations about our history E28093 both the bad parts and the good parts During a month in which we celebrate Black history we must also ensure that Black history is told and honored yearround and especially in our public schools 0D0A 0D0AOur history is dark Kevin and itE28099s difficult But thatE28099s exactly why we have to contend with it and face it head on to root out injustice and prevent it from happening again 0D0A 0D0AHereE28099s how you can help HB 1084 has just passed committee and is being sent to the State House and Senate for "Reginald Bolding (personal)" <info@reginaldbolding.com>
Jim Crow language leads to Jim Crow policies
Hey kevin  its Reginald With Black History Month coming to an end I wanted to take this time to speak with you directly Ive been the target of harassment and blatant racism from Arizonas rightwing leadership Unfortunately thats the reality that Black leaders across the country must face on a daily basis Its not just about hurtful words Jim Crow language leads to Jim Crow policies and we cant let Arizona become a place where hate and extremism thrives kevin Black leaders have worked tirelessly to advance voting rights and put their lives on the line to advocate for a more fair equitable America and I am beyond honored to continue their work and their legacies I know that we have what it takes to win and protect the future of Arizona elections from rightwing extremists like our opponent But we cant get there without your support Can I count on you to help our team reach our final goal this month We only have a couple hours left Here is a secure link to donate  Thank you for standing with me I couldnt do it without you  Reginald Reginald Bolding is running for Secretary of State to strengthen democracy in Arizona As the Democratic leader in Arizonas House of Representatives Reginald fought for economic relief criminal justice reform public education and led the charge against rightwing voter suppression Reginald will continue to defend every Arizonans right to free fair and secure elections as Arizona Secretary of State DONATE  Paid for by Friends of Reginald Bolding Authorized by Reginald Bolding Unsubscribe Sent via ActionNetworkorg                                                                   To update your email address change your name or address or to stop receiving emails from Reginald Bolding please click here

quotedprintableContentType textplain charsetUTF8Kevin As I watch RussiaE28099s invasion of Ukraine I am deeply worried about the future of our world This catastrophe should open the hearts and sharpen the resolve of all who are invested in defending democracy at home and around the globeC2A00D0A0D0AI cannot help but think of my own family and the tragedies inflicted on the people of Vietnam including the loss of life and the loss of liberty My parents fled to America as censorship book bans crackdowns on free speech and press and other antidemocratic measures became the norm I know all too well how fragile our freedoms are and how critical it is to unite in their defenseC2A00D0A0D0AThe courage and unity of the Ukrainian people inspire me E28094 especially as we remember what Ukraine symbolizes not only in relation to Europe and Russia but the role it has played in our own politics I will never forget how our former President tried to pressure Ukrainian President Zelenskyy to tip the scales in the 2020 US presidential electionC2A00D0A0D0AWhether rebuffing Trump or standing up to Vladimir Putin Zelenskyy and his people represent the best of what human beings can summon when it comes to defending our freedoms and our futures IE28099m also heartened to see the international community take swift action to hold the Russian government accountable from imposing economic sanctions and closing airspace to granting Ukraine an emergency audience before the United NationsC2A00D0A0D0AAt the same time the same discrimination so pervasive in our country is mirrored across the world with African and Indian immigrants facing barriers and danger as they flee the invasion E28094 from setbacks in boarding transportation to rejection at international borders As the daughter of Vietnamese refugees I stand with all refugees E28094 Haitian Afghan Syrian Nigerian Ukrainian and those seeking safety from humanitarian crisesC2A00D0A0D0AWhether led by Putin in Eastern Europe or by folks right at home who want to overturn our elections we are witnesses to multiple unignorable attacks on democracy and freedom with the dignity and human rights of marginalized communities as the first casualty0D0A0D0AIE28099ll be continuing to monitor this situation and I call on all who care about democracy at home and abroad not only to stand with every human being on Ukrainian soil afternoonFreedom Fighters2C The radical2C progressive governments of California2C Washington2C and Oregon recently announced that theyE28099re undoing their COVID mandates And they arenE28099t alone among the Left The CDC recently flipped the script on mask mandates2C again E2809CFollow the scienceE2809D theyE28099ll say2C but this isnE28099t science at all ItE28099s polling and Democrats worrying about the midterms And as great as that is for the children and businesses of these states2C the radical2C progressive governments of these states are still leaving the door open for future mandates after the midterms In Arizona2C we arenE28099t letting that happen I sponsored three bills to prohibit this sort of unchecked government overreach permanently and theyE28099re successfully moving forward through the Arizona legislature 09090909 09090909 JOIN OUR CAMPAIGN TO PROTECT OUR FREEDOMS2C JOIN US TODAY 09 09090909090909 SB1048 E28094 Revoking Tyrannical Emergency Powers During the pandemic2C power hungry local politicians and city mayors took it upon themselves to declare a local emergency and to close businesses This was unacceptable and caused unnecessary damage to small businesses2C workers2C and our local economies I sponsored a bill this session to retract the authority to close private business from city mayors and local politicians I firmly believe that businesses owners and workers can and should be able to make these difficult decisions for themselves HB2453 E28094 Prohibiting Governmental Entities From Requiring Masks This bill prohibits the government from denying services to anyone for refusing to wear a mask This also repeals any previous laws relating to vaccine passport prohibitions No longer will people be unable to receive the government aid and services they deserve because they choose to make their own medical choices HB2449 E28094 Prohibiting Hospitals from Denying Clergy Visitation During the pandemic2C hospitals were refusing family members and clergy from visiting sick people in their patient rooms Under this new law2C a hospital must facilitate inperson visitation for clergy2C by mandate2C if the patientE28099s death seems imminent The tragedy of isolation that COVIDhysteria brought upon America is something myself and my colleagues in the Arizona legislature do not wish to see repeated again 09090909 09090909 SUPPORT LIBERTY OVER COVID MANDATES E28094 DONATE HERE 09 09090909090909 SB1164 E28094 ProhibitingAbortion Past 15 Weeks I want to highlight one more bill that is special to me IE28099ve cosponsored legislation that will ban all abortions after the first trimester in the State of Arizona We do not have the opportunity very often to make significant steps towards an abortionfree future2C so in2C the defense of the most vulnerable Arizonans2C including the perborn2C I am very proud to have supported this bill IE28099m fighting for legislation that puts Arizonans first and protects the most vulnerable Would you sign my petitionE28094itE28099s quick and easy2C and you can do it online Petition signatures are due soon  So please sign today 09090909 09090909 SIGN MY charsetutf8ContentTransferEncoding quotedprintableGet caught up on news and events from John Eaves campaign for Georgias Secretary of State  Events UPCOMING EVENTS EFBBBFMonday March 7 2022 Qualifying Day Georgia State Capitol Atlanta EFBBBFThursday March 31 2022 End of Month Fundraising Deadline KEY DATES April 30 2022 Financial Disclosure Filing date April 25 2022 Voter registration deadline for Primary May 24 2022 Primary election date DONATE NOW How Bloody Sunday has inspired me On March 7 1965 600 civil rights protesters attempted to peacefully march across the Edmund Pettus Bridge in Selma Alabama but encountered a malicious attack from Alabama State Police on a day that is now known as Bloody Sunday These brave men and women were fighting for the right of Black Americans to vote against voter suppression laws that were present in the Jim Crow South  barriers to exercise the right to vote still exist today   One of the highlights of my political career was being invited by Congressman John Lewis to be a part of a Congressional Delegation that observed the 50th Anniversary of Bloody Sunday in Selma on March 7 2015 I was honored to march across that very bridge with President Barack Obama First Lady Michelle former President Georgia Bush and his wife Laura and Congressman John Lewis along with thousands of others from around the country   The inspiration I received that day is why I have chosen to run for Secretary of State of Georgia Simply put I want to make sure that all eligible Georgians have the right to vote in free and fair elections   On the 57th anniversary of Bloody Sunday I honor all those who fought for our right to vote but the fight to preserve the right to vote continues today IE28099m prepared to fight for this right on behalf of all Georgians Yours in Service Dr John Eaves Scenes from 50th Anniversary of Bloody Sunday in Selma Alabama Donate Give 22 to support John Eaves in 22 Our campaign to be your next Georgia Secretary of We need your help. 
 ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌

 

 

Kevin,

Just when you thought it couldn't get any worse. If you thought
Minnesota's election safeguards were bad before (no provisional
ballots, 46 days of early voting, chaotic signature rules for absentee
voting, no voter ID at the polls, mail balloting, etc.) just take a look
at what the Democrats are proposing this week in the House. Automatic
Voter Registration System legislation, HF 607
,
would open the door even wider to the risk of non-citizens registering
to vote and another, HF3666
,
ostensibly to prohibit the intimidation of election officials, could
criminalize engaged citizenry from challenging the actions or decisions
of election officials at the polls or on absentee ballot boards. We 

**need** a candidate who will get SERIOUS about using the bully pulpit
to battle against bills like these, that threaten the public trust in
our elections. Will you help us

fight for secure elections?

I have been traveling the state and making the case for Republican
delegates and independents alike: Honest and secure elections is the
most important issue our state faces if we want to have a thriving state
again! 

**I NEED YOUR HELP NOW.**

Here is how 

**YOU** can help starting today:
* GIVE $25 to help me reach legislators about safeguarding our elections

* GIVE $55 to help me run digital advertising to help recruit new
election judges

* GIVE $105 to help me reverse the mail ballot trend in Greater
Minnesota

* GIVE THE MAX to help us WIN!

Kevin, our current Secretary of State Steve Simon is on the move
and so are the Democrats. They will continue to undermine the integrity
of our elections until they have permanent control of the legislature,
the governorship, and every constitutional office. We need someone who
knows where the bodies are buried and WILL CLEAN HOUSE on day 1. That is
why I'm running. It takes more than just words to restore the office of
Secretary of State; it takes studied leadership. That's what I've done
my entire career.

Send a message! Join #TeamCrockett with a contribution of ANY amount
.
Let's battle back the DNC dollars, ZuckerBucks, and corporate special
interests! WE DON'T HAVE A REPUBLIC IF WE DON'T HAVE SECURE ELECTIONS.
Help us fight and win
.

In Freedom,

Kim Crockett

Republican Candidate for Secretary of State

DONATE TODAY AND HELP US WIN!

Standing strong with women and allies
Today is International Womens Day I am proud to stand strong with women and allies across the country and the world who have given so much of themselves to the fight for equality and justice I carry with me the sacrifices my mom made and apply those important lessons of dedication and service to my work and with my family As a single parent my mom worked tirelessly to give me everything I needed to live my American Dream in hopes that I would someday share those opportunities with those around me As my wife Cymone and I welcome a new baby girl in this world I am constantly grateful for the strong powerful women that have been incredible role models for me and push me to be the best version of myself While we continue to honor womens history this month let us also remember that there is still so much that can and should be done to promote true equality for all women and allies I am dedicated to advancing and supporting womens issues at all levels especially in the face of blatant attacks by the GOP To make a difference its going to take all of us doing our part I am honored to fight alongside powerful women and as Arizona Secretary of State I will unapologetically fight for womens issues every day Please consider supporting my campaign  every donation matters  Reginald Reginald Bolding is running for Secretary of State to strengthen democracy in Arizona As the Democratic leader in Arizonas House of Representatives Reginald fought for economic relief criminal justice reform public education and led the charge against rightwing voter suppression Reginald will continue to defend every Arizonans right to free fair and secure elections as Arizona Secretary of State DONATE  Paid for by Friends of Reginald Bolding Authorized by Reginald Bolding Unsubscribe Sent via Reginald Bolding <info@reginaldbolding.com>
As a parent and former teacher
kevin The GOP is playing politics with our education system and our children are paying the price The Governor and his band of antipublic education fanatics wasted no time running to the courts to overrule a voterapproved initiative to give muchneeded funding to our public schools As a former special education teacher and a parent of public school children I know firsthand the potential our students have if given the resources they need to succeed  and this initiative would have given them just that Its time for us to speak up and defend Arizonas children Sign on now to tell the GOP that our childrens futures are not political pawns  SAVE PUBLIC EDUCATION kevin I gave up a fullride law school scholarship to teach special education students right here in Phoenix I didnt do it because its a glamorous job or for any political points  I did it because educating and investing in our next generation is how we make the change we need to see in our communities It seems that the GOP doesnt think about whats best for Arizonans Instead they happily overturned the will of the voters to get their way They were willing to do it for Trump and now theyre doing it again putting the future of public education on the line I will not stand by while the GOP play politics with our public education system Add your name to tell the GOP our children and educators deserve better than this ADD YOUR NAME Thank you for standing with me and our public education system We couldnt do it without you  Reginald Reginald Bolding is running for Secretary of State to strengthen democracy in Arizona As the Democratic leader in Arizonas House of Representatives Reginald fought for economic relief criminal justice reform public education and led the charge against rightwing voter suppression Reginald will continue to defend every Arizonans right to free fair and secure elections as Arizona Secretary of State DONATE  Paid for by Friends of Reginald Bolding Authorized by million dollars in tax relief for renters at a critical time Conservative principles built Arizona and made it the great state it is todayI Fight for Arizona Families and Businesses2C Join Me and Kevin,

Our campaign is constantly finding ways to help citizens get engaged! We
KNOW that elections have not been fair for a long time - and Steve Simon
(D) is a huge reason why. Getting Eyes on Every Ballot

is incredibly important, but we also need to push for "voting local!"
Please watch my video on why it is so critical to return to the
time-honored tradition of in-person voting:

We saw in 2020 the pandemic used as cover to do an end-run around of our

History Month And during this month the first woman I always think about is my mother0D0A0D0AAfter all these years my motherE28099s story never fails to humble me She grew up in a wartorn country Vietnam A social worker by trade she was resourceful sewing her own wedding dress from scraps of fabric When democracy crumbled in Vietnam and civil liberties disappeared she wove baskets and rolled tobacco to help pay for my familyE28099s escape In her new country she raised five daughters E28094 what in Vietnam we call five E2809Cdragon princessesE2809D E28094 to be anything they dreamed of beingC2A00D0A0D0AThe ways women make history often live beneath the headlines They can do it through acts of heroism that often go unsung making decisions that provide a better life for their daughters supporting those daughters as they pursue unfamiliar goals my momE28099s still not thrilled about my English degree and continuously relentlessly welcoming in what is newC2A00D0A0D0A2016 marked a huge step forward for both my mother and myself she begged by her five daughters cast her firstever vote in the United States and I had my firstever conversations about running for office Six years later my mother is cheering on her daughter in the bid to become GeorgiaE28099s firstever AsianAmerican in political statewide office in a year that could be a watershed for women in Georgia E28094 a year where among other milestones we could also elect the nationE28099s firstever Black woman governorC2A00D0AC2A00D0AWomen are inextricable from the history of this state country and world and as long as we comprise over half the population we will continue to shape that history IE28099m thinking of private fighters like my mom of trailblazers like Dr Michelle Au the first AsianAmerican to serve in the Georgia State Senate of Sherry Boston the second woman ever elected as the district attorney of DeKalb County and the first DA in the country to require implicit bias training for her entire office And of course of Stacey Abrams herselfC2A00D0AC2A00D0AThere is no shortage of heroines around us We just have to pay attentionC2A00D0AC2A00D0AI want to hear more about the women in your RsbiNT1ZnHMuuLTgVbdbAA7F74207807F06426ContentTransferEncoding quotedprintableContentType texthtml charsetUTF8 This month the first woman I always think about is my mother td tbody Kevin Today is the final day of WomenE28099s History Month And during this month the first woman I always think about is my mother 0D0A After all these years my motherE28099s story never fails to humble me She grew up in a wartorn country Vietnam A social worker by trade she was resourceful sewing her own wedding dress from scraps of fabric When democracy crumbled in Vietnam and civil liberties disappeared she wove baskets and rolled tobacco to help pay for my familyE28099s escape In her new country she raised five daughters E28094 what in Vietnam we call five E2809Cdragon princessesE2809D E28094 to be anything they dreamed of being 0D0A 0D0A The ways women make history often live beneath the headlines They can do it through acts of heroism that often go unsung making decisions that provide a better life for their daughters supporting those daughters as they pursue unfamiliar goals my momE28099s still not thrilled about my English degree and continuously relentlessly welcoming in what is new 0D0A 2016 marked a huge step forward for both my mother and myself she begged by her five daughters cast her firstever vote in the United States and I had my firstever conversations about running for office Six years later my mother is cheering on her daughter in the bid to become GeorgiaE28099s firstever AsianAmerican in political statewide office in a year that could be a watershed for women in Georgia E28094 a year where among other milestones we could also elect the nationE28099s firstever Black woman governor0D0A 0D0A Women are inextricable from the history of this state country and world and as long as we comprise over half the population we will continue to shape that history  IE28099m thinking of private fighters like my mom of trailblazers like Dr Michelle Au the first AsianAmerican to serve in the Georgia State Senate of Sherry Boston the second woman ever elected as the district attorney of DeKalb County and the first DA in the country to require implicit bias training for her entire office And of course of Stacey Abrams herself0D0A There is no shortage of heroines around us We just have to pay attention I want to hear more about the women in your life who inspire and motivate you and who may even have made a bit of history themselves Hit reply to this email and tell me about them E28094 I may share your response on social media  Happy Womens History Month Bee before it gets too late

quotedprintable Mark Zuckerberg Spent Millions During the 2020 Election2C Now Hes Getting Special Tax Breaks in Idaho Over 5002C000 came to Idaho2C most to Ada County 09 09090909090909 View this email in your browser 09090909 09090909 09 09090909090909 My Fellow Idahoan2C Mark Zuckerberg spent hundreds of millions of dollars  during the 2020 election giving grants to County Clerks for PPE2C education2C and other unassuming items in every State of the Union Over 5002C000 came to Idaho2C most to Ada County Twenty Counties in total took the free money at that time of need during the COVID crisis We know too that in 20202C HB 521 2C a Bill that opened the door for capital investment in Idaho for a Data Centers2C passed the House and Senate This carveout was for companies that could invest at least 250 million for capital investment Not too many 250 million dollar investors out there with plans for Data Centers except for Facebook2C now Meta Mark Zuckerberg strikes again with a sweet deal in Idaho From the text of HB521 On and after July 12C 20202C there is exempted from the taxes imposed by this chapter the purchase or use of eligible server equipment and new data center facilities Sweet deal if youre one of the richest men on earth  And2C who picks up the tab for increased costs for supporting infrastructure for the tax base created by the incentives in the HB521 lets make a deal BillE280A6 Idaho taxpayers of course This is with the stipulation that only 30 new employee positions are createdE280A6 Do you know anybody in small business to get such a sweetheart deal I have much more to say about this and will be reporting about the under the rug sweepings that must bear the scrutiny of light Stay tuned and please watch this movie trailer coming to a theatre kevin Thank you for being a part of our powerful team of grassroots supporters We absolutely defied expectations for our first FEC report of 2022 As we keep breaking records and making history we must also keep our momentum going strong Every single donation lets us meet with one new voter make one more campaign stop and spread our message that much further Your support makes our campaign what it is  and I could not be more grateful Im running for Secretary of State because I believe that the right to vote is an essential part of being American I think the world has enough politicians we need more leaders And Im ready to stand up and lead If we are going to stand up against extremism and fight for our democracy then were going to need all hands on deck Weve only got a few more months before November and kevin  I cant wait to see what we can accomplish together for Arizona and our democracy Thank you Lets do this Reginald PS If you didnt get a chance to support our campaign last month please consider donating here  Reginald Bolding is running for Secretary of State to strengthen democracy in Arizona As the Democratic leader in Arizonas House of Representatives Reginald fought for economic relief criminal justice reform public education and led the charge against rightwing voter suppression Reginald will continue to defend every Arizonans right to free fair and secure elections as Arizona Secretary of State DONATE  Paid for by Friends of Reginald Bolding Authorized by Reginald Bolding Unsubscribe Sent via ActionNetworkorg                                                                   To update your email address change your name or address or to stop receiving emails from Reginald Bolding please click here
